<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-08T16:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-08T16:36:00-05:00" n="662" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2917</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Leavell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-08T15:00:00-06:36">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 9, 1.30
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your circular telegram of September 20, 6 p.m. Guatemalan Minister
                                for Foreign Affairs has just now informed me that the Guatemalan
                                Minister at Washington, D. C, has been instructed to publish the
                                protest of the Government of Guatemala in the sense of
                                above-mentioned circular telegram.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leavell</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>